paragraphs.text: %md ### 2) Show the 10 first rows of the prix_2016 table

result.msg: 2) Show the 10 first rows of the prix_2016 table

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT * FROM prix_2016 limit 10
%md ### 3) Number of gas stations per type of population (R: rural, A: urban, etc.)

result.msg: 3) Number of gas stations per type of population (R: rural, A: urban, etc.)

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT pop, sum(id_pdv) AS number
FROM prix_2016
GROUP BY pop
ORDER BY number DESC
%md #### The rural area is the most represented in term of gas stations.

result.msg: The rural area is the most represented in term of gas stations.

paragraphs.text: %md ## Fuel information
%md ### 4) Total receipts per fuel for the current year

result.msg: 4) Total receipts per fuel for the current year

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT nom_carburant, sum(prix) AS prix_par_carburant
FROM prix_2016
WHERE nom_carburant != ""
GROUP BY nom_carburant
ORDER BY prix_par_carburant DESC
%md #### Gazole is the most profitable fuel in France for the year 2016.

result.msg: Gazole is the most profitable fuel in France for the year 2016.

paragraphs.text: %md ### 5) Average price per fuel

%sql
SELECT nom_carburant, avg(prix) AS prix_moyen_par_carburant
FROM prix_2016
WHERE nom_carburant != ""
GROUP BY nom_carburant
ORDER BY prix_moyen_par_carburant DESC
%md #### SP98 is the most expensive fuel and E85 the cheaper, on average.

result.msg: SP98 is the most expensive fuel and E85 the cheaper, on average.

paragraphs.text: %md ## Information about the geography
%md ### 6) Select dynamically the maximum daily receipts per location

result.msg: 6) Select dynamically the maximum daily receipts per location

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT prix, latitude, longitude
FROM prix_2016
where prix <= ${maxPrix = 1000}
GROUP BY prix, latitude, longitude
ORDER BY prix DESC
%md ### 7) Top 10 profitable zip code

%sql
SELECT cp, sum(prix) AS prix
FROM prix_2016
GROUP BY cp
ORDER BY prix DESC
LIMIT 10
%md #### Zip codes 63000, 51100 and 35000 (Rennes) are the most profitable zip code.

result.msg: Zip codes 63000, 51100 and 35000 (Rennes) are the most profitable zip code.

paragraphs.text: %md ### 8) Select the Bretagne departments (22, 29, 35 and 56) and their total receipts for the current year

result.msg: 8) Select the Bretagne departments (22, 29, 35 and 56) and their total receipts for the current year

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT SUBSTR(cp, 0, 2) AS DEP, SUM(prix) AS PRIX
FROM prix_2016
WHERE SUBSTR(cp, 0, 2) IN ("22", "29", "35", "56")
GROUP BY SUBSTR(cp, 0, 2)
ORDER BY PRIX DESC
%md #### Ille-et-Vilaine department (35) is the most profitable department in Bretagne.

result.msg: Ille-et-Vilaine department (35) is the most profitable department in Bretagne.

paragraphs.text: %md ### 9) Select dynamically only one zip code (for example Bruz is 35170)

result.msg: 9) Select dynamically only one zip code (for example Bruz is 35170)

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT cp, SUM(prix) AS PRIX
FROM prix_2016
WHERE cp = ${zip = "35170"}
GROUP BY cp
%md ## Evolution over period
%md ### 10) Show the weekly receipts evolution

%sql
SELECT weekofyear(date_) AS week, sum(prix) AS prix
FROM prix_2016
WHERE date_ != ""
GROUP BY weekofyear(date_)
%md ### 11) Show the monthly receipts evolution

%sql
SELECT MONTH(date_) as mois, sum(prix) as prix
FROM prix_2016
WHERE date_ != ""
GROUP BY MONTH(date_)
%md ### 12) Line graph representing date versus price

result.msg: 12) Line graph representing date versus price

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT date_, prix
FROM prix_2016
WHERE date_ != ""
%md ### 13) Select the most profitable day of the year

result.msg: 13) Select the most profitable day of the year

paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT day(date_) AS jour, sum(prix) AS prix
FROM prix_2016
GROUP BY day(date_)
ORDER BY prix DESC
LIMIT 1
%md ## Comparison between years
%md ### 14) Merge the table prix_2016 with the tables prix_2015, prix_2014 and prix_2013

result.msg: 14) Merge the table prix_2016 with the tables prix_2015, prix_2014 and prix_2013

paragraphs.text:
%sql
CREATE TABLE prix_fusion AS
  SELECT * FROM prix_2016
  	UNION ALL
  SELECT * FROM prix_2015
	UNION ALL
  SELECT * FROM prix_2014
  	UNION ALL
  SELECT * FROM prix_2013
%md ### 15) Total receipts per year

%sql
SELECT year(date_) AS YEAR, SUM(prix) AS PRIX
FROM prix_fusion
WHERE date_ != ""
GROUP BY year(date_)
ORDER BY YEAR
%md #### The total amount of Daily Gas stations per year is increasing each year, except for 2014.

result.msg: The total amount of Daily Gas stations per year is increasing each year, except for 2014.
